-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Sigrid-Nunez-It-Will-Come-Back-to-You-The-Collected-Stories.jpg 993w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 199px) 100vw, 199px" />Sigrid Nunez, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9798217179152" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>It Will Come Back to You: The Collected Stories</em></a></strong><br />
Riverhead, July 14</h5>
<p><a href="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2026/?single=true" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>As highlighted in our first half preview:</em></a> New Sigrid Nunez! Her first short story collection! “Moving from an inappropriate teenage crush to a therapist’s second chance at love, in this collection Nunez maintains her irrepressible humor, bite and insight, while exploring the philosophical questions we have come to expect from her writing.” Spanning her career, these stories promise the same brilliant writing from one of our best writers.<em>  –Emily Firetog, Deputy Editor</em></p>
