Norton, July 21</h5>
<p><a href="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2026/?single=true" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>As highlighted in our first half preview:</em></a> From Pulitzer Prize-finalist Phillips-Fein, a book about an American tradition: fighting against equality. You read that right: within are the stories of figures like &#8220;John Adams, William Graham Sumner, Andrew Carnegie, journalist Lothrop Stoddard, Henry Ford, Harvard psychologist Richard Herrnstein, Peter Thiel, and others&#8221; who &#8220;represent this counter-tradition of hostility to democratic government.&#8221; You didn&#8217;t think it was an accident, did you?  <em>–ET</em></p>
