Doubleday, July 21</h5>
<p><a href="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2026/?single=true" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>As highlighted in our first half preview:</em></a> Whitehead caps off his Harlem Trilogy by bringing Ray Carney—business owner, former fence, family man—into the 1980s. The blurb promises a one-last-job kind of story, fitting for the conclusion to a modern classic of the crime genre.<em> –DB</em></p>
